DESCRIPTION:
lspci  is  a  utility for displaying information about PCI buses (local computer bus for attaching hardware devices in a computer. PCI is the initialism for Peripheral Component Interconnect)in the system and devices connected to them. 

By default, it shows a brief list of devices. Use the options described below  to  request  either a more verbose output or output intended for parsing by other programs.


More info: http://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/raring/man8/lspci.8.html 
